The Basic Development Set provides packages that support the development of
non-graphical applications.  In addition, it provides utilities to aid in 
the debugging of applications.  This set includes the following packages:

SOFTWARE PACKAGING TOOLS (softint)

The Software Packaging Tools package provides the tools to create packages
on a removeable media.  It also provides additional tools and libraries that
may be useful in the development process.

C OPTIMIZED COMPILATION SYSTEM (ccs)

The Optimizing C Compilation System package provides a comprehensive set of
compilation, performance analysis, source management, object file, and
debugging tools to assist in the development of new applications.

KERNEL DEBUGGER (kdb)

The Kernel Debugger package provides a utility to allow the debugging of
kernel modules and device drivers on a running computer.

ENHANCED DEBUGGER (edebug)

The Enhanced Debugger package provides a tool that helps find errors in
programs by allowing the user to control execution of a program and examine
its state.  It supports programs written in C and C++ and has an optional
MooLIT-based windowing interface.
